## SQL Analysis

Google BigQuery was used to explore and analyze the marketing campaign dataset before building the Power BI dashboard.

### Total Customers

```sql
-- Count the total number of customers

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_customers
FROM `probable-splice-491316-k1.Bank_marketing.MarketingData`;
```

---

### Overall Conversion Rate

```sql
-- Calculate overall campaign conversion rate

SELECT
    COUNT(*) AS total_customers,
    SUM(CASE WHEN y = TRUE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS subscribed_customers,
    ROUND(
        100 * SUM(CASE WHEN y = TRUE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(*),
        2
    ) AS conversion_rate_percent
FROM `probable-splice-491316-k1.Bank_marketing.MarketingData`;
```

---

### Conversion Rate by Job

```sql
-- Analyze conversion rate by customer occupation

SELECT
    job,
    COUNT(*) AS customers,
    SUM(CASE WHEN y = TRUE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS subscriptions,
    ROUND(
        100 * SUM(CASE WHEN y = TRUE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(*),
        2
    ) AS conversion_rate_percent
FROM `probable-splice-491316-k1.Bank_marketing.MarketingData`
GROUP BY job
ORDER BY conversion_rate_percent DESC;
```

---

### Conversion Rate by Age Group

```sql
-- Analyze conversion rate by age group

SELECT
    CASE
        WHEN age < 30 THEN 'Under 30'
        WHEN age BETWEEN 30 AND 39 THEN '30-39'
        WHEN age BETWEEN 40 AND 49 THEN '40-49'
        WHEN age BETWEEN 50 AND 59 THEN '50-59'
        ELSE '60+'
    END AS age_group,

    COUNT(*) AS customers,

    SUM(CASE WHEN y = TRUE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS subscriptions,

    ROUND(
        100 * SUM(CASE WHEN y = TRUE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(*),
        2
    ) AS conversion_rate_percent

FROM `probable-splice-491316-k1.Bank_marketing.MarketingData`

GROUP BY age_group

ORDER BY age_group;
```

